Overview
This workflow lets patients interact with the clinic via WhatsApp to:

View clinic information (timings, location, appointment booking instructions)
See available doctors
Browse offered services
Ask FAQs
Ask free-form questions, answered conversationally by an AI agent

Replies are sent as interactive WhatsApp list messages, with content pulled live from a Google Sheet and formatted into natural language by an LLM.
How It Works

Webhook — Receives incoming WhatsApp messages/button clicks from Meta's Cloud API.
Dedupe Check / Skip If Duplicate — Prevents duplicate processing when WhatsApp resends the same webhook event.
If — Filters out non-message events (e.g. delivery/read receipts).
Edit Fields1 — Extracts key fields (sender number, message text, button/list reply ID) from the raw payload.
If1 — Validates the extracted data before routing.
Switch (Rules) — Routes the request based on intent:

Clinic_Info — clinic details
Show_FAQ_Menu — triggered by typing "hi"
Doctors — doctor list
Services — services list
FAQ — FAQ button
Fallback — anything unmatched, sent straight to the AI agent


Edit Fields (5/3/7/6/plain) — Sets which Google Sheet category to query for each intent.
Get row(s) in sheet — Fetches the relevant data from Google Sheets.
Aggregate — Combines multiple rows into a single dataset.
AI Agent (Google Gemini / Groq) — Converts the raw data (or, for Fallback, the user's free-text question) into a natural, formatted WhatsApp reply.
Edit Fields2 — Builds the final WhatsApp Cloud API JSON payload (interactive list message format).
HTTP Request — Sends the formatted message back to the user via Meta's Graph API.

Tech Stack

n8n — workflow orchestration
WhatsApp Business Cloud API (Meta Graph API) — messaging channel
Google Sheets — content/data source (doctors, services, clinic info, FAQs)
Google Gemini / Groq — LLM for natural-language response generation

Setup

Import the workflow JSON into your n8n instance.
Connect your WhatsApp Business Cloud API credentials to the Webhook and HTTP Request nodes.
Connect your Google Sheets credentials to "Get row(s) in sheet."
Add your Google Gemini and/or Groq API credentials to the AI Agent node.
Update the Google Sheet with your clinic's doctors, services, clinic info, and FAQ content.
Activate the workflow.

Notes

WhatsApp list-reply IDs (clinic_information, doctors, services, faq) must match exactly what's configured in the Switch node rules.
The AI Agent's system prompt controls response formatting (bold headings via *text*, line breaks between sections).
